ZH: 大象是世界上最大的陆地动物。
EN: Elephants are the largest land animals in the world.

ZH: 大象的鼻子被称为象鼻。
EN: The trunk of an elephant is called a trunk.

ZH: 大象用象牙来保护自己。
EN: Elephants use their tusks to protect themselves.

ZH: 大象是草食动物。
EN: Elephants are herbivores.

ZH: 大象可以长到3米高。
EN: Elephants can grow up to 3 meters tall.

ZH: 大象可以悠闲地漫步数英里。
EN: Elephants can leisurely stroll for miles.

ZH: 大象有一个很大的身体和小耳朵。
EN: Elephants have large bodies and small ears.

ZH: 大象通过挥动耳朵来降温。
EN: Elephants cool themselves by flapping their ears.

ZH: 大象可以在水中游泳。
EN: Elephants can swim in water.

ZH: 大象是非常聪明的动物，能够学会各种技能。
EN: Elephants are very intelligent animals and can learn a variety of skills.

ZH: 大象的背上有一个驼峰。
EN: Elephants have a hump on their back.

ZH: 大象可以长时间的不喝水。
EN: Elephants can go long periods without drinking water.

ZH: 大象可以用脚来发声。
EN: Elephants can make sounds with their feet.

ZH: 大象在巨大的漩涡中可以追逐恐龙。
EN: Elephants can chase dinosaurs in a huge swirl.

ZH: 大象在森林中会吃树叶和树枝。
EN: Elephants will eat leaves and branches in the forest.

ZH: 大象会记住很多在朋友的群体中的成员。
EN: Elephants will remember many members in the group of friends.

ZH: 大象唯一怕的是老虎。
EN: Elephants are only afraid of tigers.

ZH: 大象是团体活动的动物。
EN: Elephants are social animals.

ZH: 大象可以在草原上漫步许多里程。
EN: Elephants can walk many miles on the grassland.

ZH: 大象是非常可爱的动物。
EN: Elephants are very adorable animals.
